2-7-cylindrical-and-spherical-coordinate:
In the spherical coordinate system, a point PP in space (Figure 2.97) is represented by the ordered triple (ρ,θ,φ)(ρ,θ,φ) where

ρρ (the Greek letter rho) is the distance between PP and the origin (ρ≠0);(ρ≠0);
θθ is the same angle used to describe the location in cylindrical coordinates;
φφ (the Greek letter phi) is the angle formed by the positive z-axis and line segment OP—,OP—, where OO is the origin and 0≤φ≤π.0≤φ≤π.

